### vim shortcuts
## All applicable with d (delete) as well
c + w             - Change word
c + t + character - delete everything til that character then go in insert mode
C                 - Delete til end of the line then go to insert mode 

.                 - Repeat last operation

*                 - Move through the instances of the current word in the file

0                 - go to start of the line
^                 - go to first character in the line 

t + character     - go in front of that character 
T                 - searches backward
f                 - go to that character
F                 - searches backward
;                 - find next instance of character within the line
,                 - find previous instance of character within the line

z                 - bring cursor to the middle of the screen
A                 - bring cursor to end of line in insert mode
I                 - bring cursor to start of the line in insert mode

~                 - toggle to upper/lower case

{                 - move up one hunk
}                 - move down one hunk

>> | <<           - indents in normal mode
=                 - Autoindent

q + key           - records macro in the specified key
@ + capital key   - execute macro

ctrl + v          - selects a column (similar to multi cursor)
ctrl + v + I      - add text to all columns 

KittyTerminal

Tabs
ctrl+shift+t      - new tab
ctrl+shift+q      - close tab
ctrl+shift+right  - next tab
ctrl+shift+left   - previous tab
ctrl+shift+.      - move tab forward
ctrl+shift+,      - move tab backward

Windows
ctrl+shift+enter  - new window
ctrl+shift+w      - close window
ctrl+shift+]      - next window
ctrl+shift+[      - prev window
ctrl+shift+num    - focus on specific window
